history.content:
I JUST changed a setting on one of the more hidden management screens and you should be able to at least wait list at this point.

Please note: If you are 'stuck' on a wait list it could well be that you have a time conflict between the lecture or lab section and another class. We do NOT allow time conflicts during summer session (until Sp or Fall semesters). The reason for this is that the material is very compressed, the learning experience is intense and there are no/limited tutoring resources. You really do need to attend all parts of the class to be successful.

children.subject:
IF your time conflict is caused by conflicting labs between the 2 classes, then dropping CS 70 and re-enrolling into a lab that doesn't conflict does improve your chances of getting into Data 8.

Keep in mind however that Data 8 is full and there are no plans to expand enrollment past 300 seats so you're waiting for someone to drop Data 8 before you can get in. And IF that happens, who knows which section they will drop from.

Your best path is probably to do nothing right now but keep monitoring the situation for both classes. If you see seats open up on Data 8 side and there's there's space to make changes on CS 70 side to avoid time conflict, THEN would be the time to pursue your plan.

I want to take Data 8 and CS 70 together this summer, but the only available lab sections with seats conflict. I remain on the data 8 waitlist. Is it worth re-enrolling in CS 70 and waitlisting a discussion? How should I proceed?
